						               													<description>World Tank Campaigns (WTC) is a series of tactical games that employ cards, miniatures, and boards in a fast-playing action game designed primarly for solitaire, with one-on-one action as well. WTC is the brainchild of Dana Lombardy, designer of the award winning Streets of Stalingrad.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is card driven with dice used for combat and special actions.  Combat is represented on a tactical to operational level.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;World Tank Campaigns: Bulge: Germany&amp;rsquo;s last gamble in the Ardennes to change the course of the war initially surprised the American forces, but it resulted in a major Allied victory. Each player play the role of a German or American tank commander directing a platoon of tanks with supporting forces.  The game plays out on a Battle Board unique to the scenario and tanks used in that scenario.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The World Tank Campaigns: Bulge Set has everything needed to play SOLITAIRE and 2-PLAYER games:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     2 historically accurate, incredibly detailed 1/144 scale plastic tanks&amp;#10;     Miniature tanks are pre-painted and fully assembled and include a historical information sheet about each tank&amp;#10;     2 full-color battle &amp;ldquo;boards&amp;rdquo; unique to the Ardennes and the Sherman M4A3 and Panther G tanks&amp;#10;     6 custom designed army-specic dice, plus standard d6 &amp;amp; d10&amp;#10;     88 full-color playing cards make gameplay fast and exciting&amp;#10;     55 die-cut play aid tokens (not show here), illustrated rulebook, and Quick Start Rules for the solitaire game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2 EXPANSION Sets include:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     22 additional cards, a Jagdpanzer IV tank-killer or King Tiger super heavy tank with their own unique battle boards and scenarios.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Home Page of the Game: http://www.world-tank-campaigns.com/&amp;#10;Home Page for the Miniatures: http://www.world-tank-museum.com/&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
